<title>USA: Sport Supply Q1 continuing shr loss widens.</title>
<headline>Sport Supply Q1 continuing shr loss widens.</headline>
<dateline>DALLAS 1997-03-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>1997			1996</p>
<p>Shr from continuing</p>
<p>  operations loss	 $0.18     loss	 $0.14</p>
<p>Income from continuing</p>
<p>  operations loss	 1,356     loss	   933</p>
<p> Revs			14,580		   13,216</p>
<p> Avg shrs		   7,698		    6,737</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE:  Sport Supply Group Inc said its income from continuing operations for both periods did not include losses from discontinued operations of $2,574,000, or $0.33 per share, for the first quarter of 1997 and $151,384, or $0.02 per share, for the first quarter of 1996.</p>
<p>Income from continuing operations for the first quarter of 1997 includes a writedown of the value of sold assets of approximately $2.6 million which resulted in a $1.3 million pre-tax charge.</p>
<p>The period for the first quarter of 1997 ended January 31.</p>
